1. Target Audience - The intended readership for the book.  
2. Author's Expertise - The qualifications or background of the author.  
3. Book Format - The structure or organization of the book.  
4. Subject Matter - The main topic or theme addressed in the book.  
5. Publication Date - When the book was released to the public.  
6. Marketing Approach - The strategies used to promote the book.  
7. Price Point - The cost of the book for consumers.  
8. Critical Reception - How the book is perceived by critics.  
9. Availability - Where the book can be purchased or accessed.  
10. Linguistic Style - The language and tone used in the book.  
